      "summary": "Importer upload flow bundles transport, validation, persistence, and ship bootstrap logic.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "importer/importer.go",
          "shipworkflow/urbit_operations.go",
          "docker/docker.go",
          "importer/importer_test.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`HTTPUploadHandler` in `importer/importer.go` sets headers, enforces auth/session validation, manipulates multipart chunks, handles extraction readiness, emits broadcast events, and launches container bootstrap via `configureUploadedPier`.",
          "`configureUploadedPier` and `runImportedPierWorkflow` continue the coupling by creating orchestration contexts and then starting asynchronous workflows (`beginImportedPierReadinessAndRegistration`).",
          "`beginImportedPierReadinessAndRegistration` also triggers unrelated registration/readiness flow directly after upload completion, so caller-level behavior now implicitly decides downstream lifecycle policy."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split the import pipeline into explicit stages (HTTP adapter, session validation, chunk persistence, extraction orchestration, post-import registration), each with narrow interfaces and deterministic return values, then orchestrate in one coordinator function.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
